From: tawc
Origin: own

Don't tear down the kumquat server when a single client's
process_command bubbles up an error. The original code uses `?` to
propagate per-request failures to Kumquat::run, where they short-
circuit the whole event loop and exit main(); a guest hitting an
unimplemented backend path (e.g. gfxstream's PLATFORM_AHB export,
which our `01-drop-nativewindow-dep.patch` lights up cleanly with
InvalidResourceId since the AHB-via-libnativewindow Rust shim isn't
in scope yet) takes the daemon with it. That's particularly painful
in the integration suite, where one failing test would knock kumquat
out from under every subsequent test in the same run.

Trade the panic for an eprintln + drop-this-connection: the failing
client gets EOF on its socket and surfaces the error its own way; the
next vulkaninfo / next test's connection reconnects to a healthy
server. The connection's resources die with `o.remove_entry()` →
KumquatGpuConnection::Drop, same path as a normal disconnect.

diff --git a/kumquat/server/src/kumquat.rs b/kumquat/server/src/kumquat.rs
index a4906e5..47acd43 100644
--- a/kumquat/server/src/kumquat.rs
+++ b/kumquat/server/src/kumquat.rs
@@ -56,8 +56,26 @@ impl Kumquat {
                         KumquatConnection::GpuConnection(ref mut gpu_conn) => {
                             if event.readable {
                                 if let Some(ref mut kumquat_gpu) = self.kumquat_gpu_opt {
-                                    hung_up =
-                                        !gpu_conn.process_command(kumquat_gpu)? && event.hung_up;
+                                    // tawc-fork: don't tear down the
+                                    // whole server because one client's
+                                    // request hit a backend error
+                                    // (gfxstream not implementing some
+                                    // ColorBuffer export path, etc).
+                                    // Drop just this connection; sibling
+                                    // chroots and the next reconnect
+                                    // attempt keep working.
+                                    match gpu_conn.process_command(kumquat_gpu) {
+                                        Ok(no_more_data) => {
+                                            hung_up = !no_more_data && event.hung_up;
+                                        }
+                                        Err(e) => {
+                                            eprintln!(
+                                                "kumquat: dropping connection {} after error: {:?}",
+                                                event.connection_id, e
+                                            );
+                                            hung_up = true;
+                                        }
+                                    }
                                 }
                             }
 
